        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/xesf/{size}/122_2.png",
        "created_at": "2005-06-24T12:00:57.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>These are the things we need to do, to accomplish the project.</p>\n<p><span class=\"bbcode-b\">Main things</span>:<br>\nPlot 100% complete<br>\nBasic Script 100% complete (13 chapters + 1 Alternate)<br>\nScript of Events, Quest and Riddles [in progress] (completed for the demo)<br>\nRooms design [in progress]<br>\nImages design [in progress]<br>\nDialogs implementation<br>\nVoice Casting 70% Complete (Lead Roles), 20% Complete (NPCs)<br>\nCharacter and Objects implementation<br>\nSound Effects<br>\nMusics 70-80% complete<br>\nConcept Art [in progress]<br>\nStory Code [testing some cutscenes]</p>\n<p><span class=\"bbcode-b\">Things to grab during the above items</span>:<br>\nList of Objects. (28 max) [in progress]<br>\nList of Game Flags. (inventory items used, quests to do) [according with events/riddle script]<br>\nList of Chapters. [in progress] (2 chapters)<br>\nList of Magic Levels [done] (same as LBA1)<br>\nList of Locations [in progress]<br>\nList of Holomap Locations [in progress]<br>\nList of Disappearing Grids.<br>\nList of Dialogs and his indexs.<br>\nList of Character Names. [in progress]<br>\nList of Characters Per Location. [in progress]<br>\nList of Actions will each character have during the quest.<br>\nList of Character Definitions (life points, strenght, etc and which dialogs each only will use).<br>\nList of Character Animations<br>\nList of Sprites / Bricks<br>\nList of Midis<br>\nList of Samples</p>\n<p><span class=\"bbcode-b\">In Plain English (08.08.07):</span><br>\nWeve completed a number of new script chapters since the last update, and have sketched out a rough version of the plot to near game completion. Concept art is constant, and Luke has done a great job, especially with storyboarding. Similarly, we have some great renders from LG. The grids from Zink, Alex, Obras, and now Jesse too are very good, and Alex and Zink are continuing work on programs. Were much further than we were 6 months ago. The project is still on pace for a late 2007 release, and we should begin recording final voices sometime in the fall.</p>\n<p>The script/plot are finally complete! We now know exactly what Hegesippe does, why he does it, and how it happens. Hoorah. Luke has also pounded out some great concept art that is allowing us to work on grids and character models very nicely. Currently, we are planning a Demo release sometime for late August/early September (a hard release date will be coming soon). Also, keep sending us your voice auditions, MBNers. We need as many people as possible to fill in the thousands of NPCs across Twinsun! <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
